I use a lot of Starbucks, more than once a day, and this one is the most disappointing. Today, for example. I watched the Barista make several coffees and in each instance when he rinsed out the canister or pitcher then he turned it up quick out of the water leaving dirty water in the bottom and went right into the next drink with..dirty nasty water in the bottom of the canister IN EVERY CUP! I called him out on it & he argued with me. I offered to call the health department since he didn't want to change his nasty ways.  Then I ordered a cascade cold foam brew. I watched...I got coffee and foam and that's it. I asked about the cascade sprinkle for the top, "oh it's Monday, I forgot", then he put it on. I went to cashier and ask about the lack of sweetness, he said "oh it should have vanilla syrup" and put it in. No cascara syrup went in at all!  If you go here WATCH every move made or you'll be drinking dirty dish water and you'll get charged for a drink incorrectly made.

I order my coffee the same at every Starbucks that I frequent and have never had an issue but Raseanda decides today that she wants to charge me for adding milk to my double expresso.  I tell her this is the way that I have always ordered it and never have had an issue.  She proceeds to tell me that there is a charge and this one time she will give me extra milk.  She pours a shot of milk in my coffee and then throws the rest of the milk in the sink.  I tell her that's not enough and just give me a refund.....so you'd rather waste milk by throwing it away rather than giving it to me?  This Raseanda seems to be on a power trip and always have a nasty attitude.  She is not very welcoming and does not belong in customer service.

And where a non-Starbucks regular I was with was told that the soy milk for her coffee was at the bar with the milk and sugar: no, it's not; it never is, in any Starbucks anywhere.
